<p>I have a certificate and I have written the below python code to fetch the thumbprint of the cert file:     certificate = "C:\global.crt"</p>  <pre><code>certp = open(certificate, 'r') tempcert = certp.read().strip() certp.close() tempcert =  re.sub('-----.*?-----', '', tempcert) tempcert = re.sub('\n', '', tempcert) tempcert = base64.b64decode(tempcert) print hashlib.sha1(tempcert).hexdigest() </code></pre>  <p>The above code is giving me the thumbprint. But when I open the certificate file on my windows server directly and check the details, the thumbprint shown is different. </p>  <p>Am I doing some mistake in my python code? Why is the thumbprint different?</p>